network.param

Class NetworkManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • network.param.NetworkManager

  • public final class NetworkManager
extends java.lang.Object
    An entry class to access ParamNetwork, using this class you can able to access all the param modules.

    NetworkManager is a singleton class using this class you can able to access all the param modules.

     NetworkManager networkManager = NetworkManager.getInstance();
 INodeConfig networkConfig = new NodeConfig("< NODE_URL >", "< PRIVATE_KEY >"); //Init config.
 networkManager.setNetworkConfig(INodeConfig networkConfig) //Add config to network manager.

    NetworkManager defines below categories of operations:

    • Method getInstance returns the NetworkManager Object.

    • Method setNetworkConfig will set network.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Jitendra Kumar Balla, ParamNetwork

    • Method Detail

      • getInstance

        public static NetworkManager getInstance()
        This method will return NetworkManager Object.

        Returns the NetworkManager object associated with the ParamNetwork SDK. Most of the methods of class NetworkManager are instance methods and must be invoked with respect to the current NetworkManager object.

        Returns:
        NetworkManager the NetworkManager object associated with SDK.

      • setNetworkConfig

        public void setNetworkConfig(INodeConfig networkConfig)
                      throws ConfigExistsException
        Loads the specified NetworkConfig to SDK.

        Using this method you can able to set INodeConfig, Currently you can able to set config only once. If you want to reset the config, then use reset().

        Parameters:
        networkConfig - network config for NetworkManager
        Throws:
        ConfigExistsException - Config exists then it will throw ConfigExistsException
